Good Morning! I've got a quick question - Do you have any family traditions? We have a couple! #sponsored One of our favorite traditions is making sure whenever we head out on our adventures we check in at a local fruit stand to stock up on the goods! üçåüççü••This is one of our all-time favorite things to do as a family and we have so many fun memories. I love that our traditions can even be daily ones! For us traditions create a bond that comes from feeling that we're part of something unique and special. When I was little my dad would bring my siblings to the local market to pick out a treat before school and he told us the reason he did this was because his father did the same! I have so many beautiful memories with my dad‚Äôs father 'Papa Earl'. On @ancestry I was able to dig deeper into his past and find out that he was a woodworker and built his own furniture. His father taught him and it goes back for generations. We have so many traditions in our family whether its daily, weekly or lifelong ones! What family traditions do you want to pass down for generations? I'd love to know! #questionsandancestors

If you could go back in time to spend a day in the life of one ancestor from any time period, who would you choose and why? #sponsored I‚Äôd choose my Grandma Josephine, who passed away before I was born. Family is a huge part of my life, which is why I wanted to discover more about her on @ancestry. I learned that after she was orphaned in 1936, when she was only 12-years old, she moved from Oklahoma to Los Angeles to live with her oldest brother (swipe to see the 1940 census record I found as proof). To experience what she went through in life would give me a new perspective on my family history. Sometimes we forget that the experiences of the people who came before us brought us to this moment in time. This photo with my children on the beach is proof that dreams can come true! I'll always look back at these beach days and cherish them until the end of time, and I hope my grandma is smiling down at us. Now I‚Äôd love to hear whose shoes you‚Äôd want to walk in from your family tree. #QuestionsAndAncestors
